body_html:
I am trying to build the more recent libhexagon_nn_skel.so version mentioned in TF-HVX, however, I am having a compilation error:


make[1]: Entering directory `/home/aashouri/Qualcomm/Hexagon_SDK/3.0/examples/common/nnlib'
ERROR: Could not open file (/prj/dsp/qdsp6/arch/cnn/setup/inceptionv3_uint8in.c)
make[1]: *** [android_Release/inceptionv3_uint8in.o] Error 255

Working around the issue by defining a dummy input data as mentioned by @satok16 here did not solve my issue either. Unless

make tree VERBOSE=1 V=hexagon_Release_dynamic_toolv72_v60

will suffice to complete the toolchain.

There are many combinations of versions between Qualcomm SDK (3.0, 3.1, 3.2 and 3.3.3) and libbnn available. A clarification on the compatible versions with and also to Tensorflow build system would be appreciated.

body:
I am trying to build the more recent `libhexagon_nn_skel.so` version mentioned in [TF-HVX](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/contrib/hvx/), however, I am having a compilation error: 

```

make[1]: Entering directory `/home/aashouri/Qualcomm/Hexagon_SDK/3.0/examples/common/nnlib'
ERROR: Could not open file (/prj/dsp/qdsp6/arch/cnn/setup/inceptionv3_uint8in.c)
make[1]: *** [android_Release/inceptionv3_uint8in.o] Error 255

```

Working around the issue by defining a dummy input data as mentioned by @satok16 [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/9428) did not solve my issue either. Unless

 ```
make tree VERBOSE=1 V=hexagon_Release_dynamic_toolv72_v60

```
will suffice to complete the toolchain.

There are many combinations of versions between `Qualcomm SDK (3.0, 3.1, 3.2 and 3.3.3)` and `libbnn` available. A clarification on the compatible versions with and also to Tensorflow build system would be appreciated.
